cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper deals with unsupervised image-to-image translation, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a framework that involves learning and modeling the conditional distribution of images, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with multimodal image translation, which involves multiple modes of data, and hence, could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves analyzing and establishing theoretical results, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
